$(time)

Grabs the current local time for the Time Zone you specify

Parameters
This variable requires one variable, the time zone. If you specify an invalid time zone, the command will default to UTC. 

Example Output: 

$(time America/Los_Angeles)

Example Response: 15:11:04 (PST)

Error Output: 

$(time Austraya)

Error Response: 18:02:44 (UTC)

List of Time Zones: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones
